# SOPv5.1 Continuous Demo Test User Guide

**Version**: 5.1.0  
**Date**: 2025-07-31 09:10:36 CEST  
**Status**: Production Ready  

## Overview

The SOPv5.1 Continuous Enterprise Demo system provides comprehensive testing and validation of the Intelitor Security Monitoring System using cybernetic goal-oriented execution framework with TPS methodology integration.

## Quick Start Commands

### Basic Demo Execution

```bash
# Standard 2-hour continuous demo (Container-Aware)
PHICS_ENABLED=true elixir scripts/demo/container_aware_continuous_demo.exs 2.0

# Quick 30-minute demo for presentations  
PHICS_ENABLED=true elixir scripts/demo/container_aware_continuous_demo.exs 0.5

# Enterprise-grade demo with full monitoring (UPDATED)
PHICS_ENABLED=true elixir scripts/demo/container_aware_continuous_demo.exs --comprehensive --enterprise --monitoring

# Legacy SOP v5.1 demo (still available)
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --comprehensive
```

### Demo Test Validation

```bash
# Run the demo test suite (validates all components)
mix test test/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo_test.exs

# Run with detailed output
mix test test/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo_test.exs --trace

# Run with coverage analysis
mix test test/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo_test.exs --cover
```

## Comprehensive Command Reference

### Core Demo Commands

#### 1. Standard Demo Execution
```bash
# Basic continuous demo (2 hours)
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs

# With specific duration
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --duration 120

# With git tracking enabled
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --git-tracking
```

#### 2. Enterprise Demo Modes
```bash
# Full enterprise demonstration
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --comprehensive --enterprise

# With performance monitoring
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --comprehensive --monitoring

# With analytics export
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --comprehensive --analytics-export
```

#### 3. Targeted Demo Categories
```bash
# Security workflows only
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --category security

# Mobile API demonstration
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --category mobile

# Real-time monitoring focus
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --category realtime

# Multi-tenant validation
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --category multitenant

# Performance testing
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --category performance
```

### Test Validation Commands

#### 1. Comprehensive Test Suite
```bash
# Run all demo tests
mix test test/demo/

# Run with TDG validation
mix test test/demo/ --tdg-compliance

# Run with parallel execution
mix test test/demo/ --parallel --max-cases 4
```

#### 2. Specific Test Categories
```bash
# Container health tests
mix test test/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo_test.exs -t container_health

# Performance validation tests
mix test test/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo_test.exs -t performance

# STAMP safety constraint tests
mix test test/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo_test.exs -t stamp_safety
```

#### 3. Continuous Integration Tests
```bash
# Pre-commit validation
mix test test/demo/ --pre-commit

# CI/CD pipeline tests
mix test test/demo/ --ci-mode --export-results

# Quality gate validation
mix test test/demo/ --quality-gates --strict
```

### Advanced Demo Configuration

#### 1. Multi-Agent Coordination
```bash
# With 11-agent architecture
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --agents 11 --supervisor 1 --helpers 4 --workers 6

# With dynamic token optimization
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --dynamic-tokens --optimization adaptive

# With patient supervision mode
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --patient-mode --timeout 7200
```

#### 2. Container Integration
```bash
# Force container execution
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --container-only

# With PHICS hot-reloading
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --phics-enabled

# Container health monitoring
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --container-health-monitoring
```

#### 3. Performance and Monitoring
```bash
# With real-time metrics
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --real-time-metrics

# Export performance data
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --export-performance

# With comprehensive logging
elixir scripts/demo/sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo.exs --verbose-logging --log-level debug
```

## Status and Monitoring Commands

### Real-time Status Checking
```bash
# Check container-aware demo status (UPDATED)
ps aux | grep container_aware_continuous_demo

# Check legacy demo status
ps aux | grep sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo

# Monitor system resources
htop

# Check standardized container status (UPDATED)
podman ps -a --filter name=intelitor-*-demo

# Database connectivity (Standardized naming)
pg_isready -h localhost -p 5433 -U postgres
```

### Container Infrastructure Status (UPDATED)
```bash
# Check all demo containers
podman ps --filter name=intelitor-postgres-demo
podman ps --filter name=intelitor-redis-demo
podman ps --filter name=intelitor-prometheus-demo
podman ps --filter name=intelitor-grafana-demo

# Check Phoenix server and LiveDashboard access
curl -I http://localhost:4000
curl -I http://localhost:4000/dev/dashboard

# Verify service ports
netstat -tuln | grep -E ":400[01]|:5433|:6379|:9090|:3000"
```

### Demo Progress Monitoring
```bash
# Tail container-aware demo logs (UPDATED)
tail -f /tmp/container_demo_execution.log

# Tail Phoenix compilation logs
tail -f /tmp/phoenix.log

# Monitor git commits (if git tracking enabled)
git log --oneline --since="1 hour ago"

# Check performance metrics
cat /tmp/demo_performance_metrics.json

# LiveDashboard monitoring (NEW)
open http://localhost:4000/dev/dashboard
```

### LiveDashboard Access (NEW SECTION)
```bash
# Primary LiveDashboard access
curl http://localhost:4000/dev/dashboard

# Check LiveDashboard availability
if curl -s http://localhost:4000/dev/dashboard > /dev/null; then
  echo "✅ LiveDashboard operational"
  open http://localhost:4000/dev/dashboard
else
  echo "⏳ Phoenix still compiling, checking status..."
  tail -5 /tmp/phoenix.log
fi

# Port 4001 proxy setup (if needed)
elixir scripts/demo/port_4001_proxy.exs
```

## Troubleshooting Commands

### Common Issues Resolution
```bash
# Fix compilation issues before demo
export ELIXIR_ERL_OPTIONS="+S 16"
mix compile --warnings-as-errors

# Validate factory integrity
mix test test/support/factories/ --trace

# Reset demo environment (UPDATED)
elixir scripts/demo/reset_demo_environment.exs

# Container naming standardization fix (NEW)
podman stop test-postgres test-redis 2>/dev/null || true
podman rm test-postgres test-redis 2>/dev/null || true

# Validate TDG compliance
elixir scripts/tdg/gates/pre_commit_validation.sh
```

### Phoenix and LiveDashboard Issues (NEW SECTION)
```bash
# Check Phoenix compilation status
tail -10 /tmp/phoenix.log

# Force restart Phoenix with clean compilation
pkill -f "mix phx.server" || true
export DATABASE_URL=postgres://postgres:postgres@localhost:5433/intelitor_demo
export REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379
export PHICS_ENABLED=true
export ELIXIR_ERL_OPTIONS="+S 16"
nohup mix phx.server > /tmp/phoenix.log 2>&1 &

# Test Phoenix availability
sleep 30 && curl -I http://localhost:4000

# Test LiveDashboard specifically
curl http://localhost:4000/dev/dashboard

# Port 4001 troubleshooting
# Note: LiveDashboard is accessible at localhost:4000/dev/dashboard
# Port 4001 can be proxied if needed using scripts/demo/port_4001_proxy.exs
```

### Emergency Recovery
```bash
# Stop running demos safely (UPDATED)
pkill -f container_aware_continuous_demo || true
pkill -f sop_v51_continuous_enterprise_demo || true
pkill -f "mix phx.server" || true

# Clean up containers (preserve demo containers)
podman stop $(podman ps -q --filter name=temp) 2>/dev/null || true
# Note: Keep intelitor-*-demo containers running for demos

# Reset database (with container awareness)
export DATABASE_URL=postgres://postgres:postgres@localhost:5433/intelitor_demo
mix ash.setup --reset

# Validate system health (UPDATED)
elixir scripts/validation/system_health_check.exs

# Full container infrastructure restart (if needed)
podman restart intelitor-postgres-demo intelitor-redis-demo intelitor-prometheus-demo intelitor-grafana-demo
```

## Prerequisites Validation

### System Requirements Check
```bash
# Verify Elixir version
elixir --version  # Should be 1.18+

# Check PostgreSQL
pg_isready -h localhost -p 5433

# Validate Podman
podman --version  # Should be 5.4.1+

# Confirm Git repository
git status
```

### Dependency Validation
```bash
# Install dependencies
mix deps.get

# Compile without warnings
mix compile --warnings-as-errors

# Run basic tests
mix test --only basic

# Validate database migrations
mix ash.setup
```

## Performance Optimization

### Resource Configuration
```bash
# Optimize for performance
export ELIXIR_ERL_OPTIONS="+S 16"

# Enable patient mode for reliability
export CLAUDE_PATIENT_MODE=true
export CLAUDE_TIMEOUT=7200000

# Container optimization
export CONTAINER_OPTIMIZE=true
```

### Memory and CPU Tuning
```bash
# Monitor resource usage during demo
watch -n 5 'ps aux --sort=-%cpu | head -10'

# Memory monitoring
watch -n 5 'free -h'

# Container resource monitoring
podman stats
```

## Best Practices

### Before Running Demo
1. **Validate Prerequisites**: Ensure all dependencies are installed and configured
2. **Clean Environment**: Reset containers and database to known state
3. **Check Git Status**: Ensure clean working directory
4. **Validate Factories**: Run factory tests to ensure data generation works
5. **Test Compilation**: Ensure zero-warning compilation

### During Demo Execution
1. **Monitor Logs**: Keep an eye on demo execution logs
2. **Watch Resources**: Monitor CPU, memory, and container health
3. **Track Progress**: Monitor demo cycle completion and performance metrics
4. **Validate STAMP**: Ensure safety constraints are continuously met

### After Demo Completion
1. **Review Metrics**: Analyze performance and success metrics
2. **Check Logs**: Review any warnings or errors in logs
3. **Validate Results**: Ensure all demo categories completed successfully
4. **Document Findings**: Record any issues or improvements identified
5. **Clean Up**: Stop processes and clean up temporary resources

## Success Metrics

### Expected Performance Indicators
- **Demo Cycles**: 20-30 cycles per minute
- **Container Health**: 100% healthy status maintained (intelitor-*-demo containers)
- **Error Rate**: <0.5% across all operations
- **Response Times**: <50ms average API response
- **Resource Usage**: CPU <50%, Memory <4GB
- **Phoenix Availability**: localhost:4000 responsive <2 seconds
- **LiveDashboard**: localhost:4000/dev/dashboard operational

### Quality Gates
- **STAMP Safety**: All 5 constraints validated
- **TDG Compliance**: 100% test-driven generation adherence
- **Zero Warnings**: No compilation warnings tolerated
- **Container Native**: 100% container-only execution (standardized naming)
- **Multi-Agent**: 11-agent coordination operational
- **PHICS Integration**: Hot-reloading functional in container environment
- **Database Connectivity**: PostgreSQL on port 5433 responsive
- **Monitoring Stack**: Prometheus (9090) and Grafana (3000) operational

